Commented on #570 Add range checking for internal holograms

@filoghost Any plans for introducing this in the current version? Seems like there are getters exposed for that already: https://github.com/filoghost/HolographicDisplays/blob/5727de44dcdbf85bd36aae5ebec86ff52f2a3679/core/src/main/java/me/filoghost/holographicdisplays/core/tracking/TextLineTracker.java#L117-L120 Unfortunately, with the hard-coded distance of 64, holograms are visible from far through walls. Seems like there is no way to change the tracking range, as holograms are now packet based (previously possible via spigot.yml). It would be awesome to have per-hologram view ranges, as this allows the hologram, when the player approaches it, to act more like a tooltip, a call to action of some kind. Feels like a great way to enhance UX for players, as opposed to a single view range, which introduces a lot of unnecessary clutter and made me avoid using holograms in the past.
